<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Seventeenth session 
</b>Agenda item 3  
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, 
civil, political, economic, social and cultural rights,  
including the right to development  
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on the promotion and 
protection of the right to freedom of opinion and expression, 
Frank La Rue 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Mission to Mexico</b>* **<b> 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i> The Special Rapporteur visited Mexico from 9 to 24 August 2010, at the 
Government&#8217;s invitation, on an official joint mission with the Special Rapporteur for 
Freedom of Expression of the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights (IACHR), 
Ms. Catalina Botero. This was the first joint official visit made by the two Rapporteurs. The 
Special Rapporteur acknowledges the openness of the Mexican State in inviting them to 
visit the country and emphasizes its cooperation before, during and after their visit. In 
addition to the Federal District, the visit included the states of Chihuahua, Guerrero, 
Sinaloa and Mexico. The Special Rapporteur held meetings with governmental, legislative 
and judicial authorities at both federal and state level and with civil society organizations, 
journalists&#8217; organizations and other relevant stakeholders. 
</p>
<p> The report analyses the legal framework and the historical and political context of 
freedom of opinion and expression and access to information in Mexico. It describes the 
current situation of violence and impunity, exemplified by the fact that very few of the 66 
cases of murder of journalists that occurred between 2000 and December 2010 have been 
solved. Incomplete investigations in the vast majority of cases prevent an exact 
</p>
<p>  
 * The summary of this report is being circulated in all official languages. The report itself, 
</p>
<p>which is annexed to the summary, is being circulated in the language of submission and 
English only. 
</p>
<p> ** Late submission. 
</p>
<p> United Nations A/HRC/17/27/Add.3
